ww.aish.com/jewishissues/middleeast/Bernard_Lewis_Unplugged.asp |title=Archived copy |access-date=29 December 2005 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20051215151652/http://www.aish.com/jewishissues/middleeast/Bernard_Lewis_Unplugged.asp |archive-date=15 December 2005 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> historian\n* [[David Malcolm Lewis]], professor of history, [[University of Oxford]]<ref>JYB 1995 p193</ref>\n* [[Hyam Maccoby]], professor of history<ref>{{cite web|url=http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4158/is_20040504/ai_n12778519 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-05-25 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150909024326/http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4158/is_20040504/ai_n12778519 |archivedate= 9 September 2015 }}</ref>\n* [[Sir Philip Magnus, 1st Baronet]], educationalist and politician\n* [[Sir Philip Magnus-Allcroft, 2nd Baronet]],<ref>Encyclopaedia Judaica, art. \"Magnus\"</ref> biographer\n* [[Shula Marks]], expert on African history<ref name=\"JYB 2005 p215\"/>\n* [[Arnaldo Momigliano]], professor of history, [[University College London]]<ref name=\"JYB 1985 p188\">JYB 1985 p188</ref>\n* [[Lewis Bernstein Namier]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.factmonster.com/ce6/people/A0834786.html |title=Namier, Sir Lewis Bernstein |publisher=FactMonster |date= |accessdate=2018-07-19}}</ref> historian (converted to Anglicanism)\n* [[Francis Palgrave|Sir Francis Palgrave]] (born ''[[Cohen (surname)|Cohen]]'') (1768\u20131861),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fromoldbooks.org/Wood-NuttallEncyclopaedia/p/palgravesirfrancis.html |title=Palgrave, Sir Francis (Nuttall Encyclop\u00e6dia) |publisher=Fromoldbooks.org |date= |accessdate=2018-07-19}}</ref> UK historian\n*[[Ilan Papp\u00e9]] Israeli born [[New Historian]] , author of [[The Ethnic Cleansing of Palestine]] and professor at The [[University of Exeter]]\n* Sir [[Michael Postan]], historian<ref name=\"JYB 1985 p188\"/>\n* [[Cecil Roth]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.jhom.com/personalities/dona_gracia/roth.htm |title=Archived copy |access-date=29 December 2005 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060318201126/http://www.jhom.com/personalities/dona_gracia/roth.htm |archive-date=18 March 2006 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> historian and editor of the ''Encyclopaedia Judaica''\n* [[Simon Schama]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.age-of-the-sage.org/history/historian/Simon_Schama.html |title=Simon Schama History of Britain |publisher=Age-of-the-sage.org |date= |accessdate=2018-07-19}}</ref> historian\n* [[Leonard Schapiro]],<ref>[[Concise Dictionary of National Biography]]: \"born in Glasgow of an Anglophile Riga Jewish family\"</ref> historian\n* [[Simon Sebag Montefiore]],<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070714100413/http://www.randomhouse.com/vintage/catalog/display.pperl?isbn=9781400076789&view=qa Vintage Catalog | Stalin by Simon Sebag Montefiore<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> historian.\n* [[Charles Singer]],<ref>[[Encyclopaedia Judaica]], art. Historians, list headed \"Prominent Jewish General Historians\"</ref> historian of science\n* [[Aurel Stein|Sir Aurel Stein]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0295977302 |title=Aurel Stein: Pioneer of the Silk Road: Annabel Walker: 9780295977300: Amazon.com: Books |publisher=Amazon.com |date= |accessdate=2018-07-19}}</ref> archeologist\n* [[Barry Supple]], British economic historian<ref>Jewish Year Book, 2005, p.&nbsp;215</ref>\n* [[Geza Vermes]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/rn/relig/spirit/stories/s47729.htm|title=:\"Five years or so later, I decided to define publicly my identity as belonging to the Jewish community by becoming a member of the Liberal Jewish Synagogue.\"|access-date=25 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110514050933/http://www.abc.net.au/rn/relig/spirit/stories/s47729.htm|archive-date=14 May 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n===Medical===\n<!--PLEASE DO NOT ADD ANY MORE NAMES TO THIS PAGE WITHOUT 