er 2004 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> legal philosopher\n* [[Brian Klug]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/main.jhtml?xml=/news/2007/02/05/njews105.xml |title=News: Breaking stories & updates |publisher=Telegraph.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2018-07-19}}</ref> Senior Research Fellow in Philosophy, St Benet's Hall, University of Oxford; concepts of race, antisemitism, Islamophobia, Jewish identity\n* [[Stephan Korner]], Bristol professor of philosophy<ref name=\"JYB 2005 p215\"/>\n* [[Imre Lakatos]],<ref>Oxford [[Dictionary of National Biography]]: \"the only child of Jacob M\u00e1rton Lipsitz, a wine merchant, and M\u00e1rgit Herczfeld, both Hungarian Jews\"</ref> Hungarian-born philosopher\n* [[Alexander Piatigorsky]],<ref>{{cite news|author=Tudor Parfitt |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2010/jan/05/alexander-piatigorsky-obituary |title=Alexander Piatigorsky obituary &#124; World news |newspaper=The Guardian |accessdate=2018-07-19}}</ref> philosopher, Buddhologist, writer\n* [[Karl Popper|Sir Karl Popper]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.britac.ac.uk/pubs/src/popper/part1.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2005-12-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051230105544/http://www.britac.ac.uk/pubs/src/popper/part1.html |archivedate=30 December 2005 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> philosopher of science (family became Lutheran)\n* [[Jonathan Romain]], minister of Maidenhead Jewish community and leader of the British reform movement\n* [[Richard Rudolf Walzer]]<ref name=\"JYB 1975 p214\"/>\n* [[Ludwig Wittgenstein]], philosopher; Jewish grandparents on both sides of the family who had converted to Christianity in the 19th century; he was christened, raised and eventually buried as a Catholic\n* [[Richard Wollheim]]<ref>[http://www.waywiser-press.com/wollheim.html \"Wollheim was an outstanding representative of a generation of Central European Jewish intellectuals\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20041011185540/http://www.waywise