ston: The BBC reporter who means business|work=The Jewish Chronicle|date=21 February 2008|accessdate=8 March 2020}}</ref> TV reporter\n* [[Melanie Phillips]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://jewishreviewofbooks.com/articles/4989/freethinker/|title=Freethinker|last=Hernroth-Rothstein|first=Annika|date=Winter 2019|accessdate=21 March 2020|work=Jewish Review of Books}}</ref> journalist\n* [[Stephen Pollard]],<ref name=indy1>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/media/press/fantastic-timing-a-baptism-of-fire-at-the-jewish-chronicle-1299058.html|title='Fantastic timing': a baptism of fire at the Jewish Chronicle|last=Bell|first=Matthew|date=11 January 2009|accessdate=26 September 2019|work=The Independent}}</ref> editor and journalist\n* [[Gail Rebuck]], Publisher [www.independent.co.uk/life-style/interview-gail-warning-1154352.html]\n* [[Paul Reuter]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ejpress.org/article/in_depth/on_anglo_jewry/3810 |title=Archived copy |access-date=29 December 2005 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060427034731/http://www.ejpress.org/article/in_depth/on_anglo_jewry/3810 |archive-date=27 April 2006 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> founder of [[Reuters]]\n* [[Rachel Riley]],<ref>https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/rachel-riley-of-countdown-finds-her-jewish-roots-to-take-on-the-corbynistas-7hdmshx7f</ref> television presenter and co-host of ''[[Countdown (game show)|Countdown]]''\n* [[Jacob Rothschild, 4th Baron Rothschild]], Non-Executive Deputy Chairman of the Board, British SKY Broadcasting Group PLC<ref>The Times (London); 3 December 1992; [[Ruth Gledhill]]:'Lord Rothschild, who is head of the English branch of the Rothschild family, says: \"I would not like to disguise that I am first and foremost a secular Jew.\"'</ref>\n* [[Joshua Rozenberg]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2015/dec/17/marriage-law-commission-reform-marry-outdoors|title=UK marriage law is out of step with the times|last=Rozenberg|f