ritish chess player\n* [[Victor Wahltuch]],<ref name=\"foonews\" /> British chess player\n* [[Baruch Harold Wood]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.anusha.com/alekhine.htm|title=Alekhine Controversy - Articles written by the World Chess Champion in 1941|website=www.anusha.com}}</ref> British chess player\n* [[Johannes Zukertort]],<ref name=\"chess\" /> Polish/German/British chess player\n\n===Cricket===\n* [[Mike Barnard]], England, cricketer\n* [[Mark Bott]], England, cricketer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.the-jc.com/sport/sport-news/team-gb-cricket-fail-see-job-through|author=Danny Caro |title=Team GB cricket fail to see the job through  |work=The Jewish Chronicle |date=14 July 2009 |accessdate=1 July 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Darren Gerard]], England, cricketer<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.times-series.co.uk/sport/611591.blues_pack_british_squad/ |title=Blues pack British squad |work=The Times |date=6 July 2005 |accessdate=1 July 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Steven Herzberg]], English-born Australian, cricketer<ref name=\"cricinfo1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cricinfo.com/other/content/story/352132.html|author= Ajay S Shankar|title=Rhodes to be part of unique Israel team|publisher=ESPN Cricinfo |date= 23 May 2008|accessdate=1 July 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Bev Lyon]], England, cricketer\n* [[Dar Lyon]], England, cricketer (brother of Bev)\n* [[John Raphael (sportsman)|John Raphael]], England, batsman\n* [[Fred Trueman]], cricketer (Jewish ancestry)<ref>''[[Jewish Chronicle]]'' 7 July 2006 p40: \"T'fastest Jewish bowler ever\"</ref>\n\n===Fencing===\n* [[Allan Jay]], British (\u00e9p\u00e9e and foil), Olympic two-time silver, world champion\n* [[Edgar Seligman]] (1867\u20131958), British (\u00e9p\u00e9e, foil, and sabre), Olympic two-time silver (\u00e9p\u00e9e), two-time British champion in each weapon\n\n===Football (association, soccer)===\n*[[David Beckham]], England, retired footballer<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2007/jul/14/newsstory.losangelesgalaxy|title=