wish Chronicle |date= |accessdate=24 May 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Alan Menter]], England/South Africa, {{nrut|South Africa}} national team\n* [[John Raphael (sportsman)|John Raphael]], Belgium/England, {{nrut|England}} national team\n\n===Sailing===\n* [[Tony Bullimore]], British, yachtsman<ref>\"Bullimore's sister buoyed by rabbis' support\", ''[[Jewish Chronicle]]'' 24 January 1997, p. 1</ref>\n* [[Peter Jaffe]], Great Britain, Olympic silver (yachting; star-class)\n\n===Table tennis===\n* [[Viktor Barna]] (born \"Gy\u0151z\u0151 Braun\"), Hungary/Britain, 22-time world champion, International Table Tennis Foundation Hall of Fame (ITTFHoF)\n* [[Richard Bergmann]], Austria/Britain, seven-time world champion, ITTFHoF\n* [[Benny Casofsky]], English Swaythling Cup player\n* [[Jeff Ingber]]\n* [[Hyman Lurie]], English three-time world bronze medallist\n* [[Ivor Montagu]], Britain, national team\n\n===Tennis===\n* [[Angela Buxton]], England, won 1956 [[French Championships|French]] Women's Doubles (w/[[Althea Gibson]]) and 1956 [[Wimbledon Championships|Wimbledon]] Women's Doubles (w/Gibson), highest world ranking # <nowiki>9</nowiki><ref name=\"google17\">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dDyEVDIA3aIC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false |author= Peter S. Horvitz|title=The Big Book of Jewish Sports Heroes: An Illustrated Compendium of Sports History and The 150 Greatest Jewish Sports Stars|publisher=SP Books |year=2007 |accessdate=4 June 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"tennisgrandstand3\">{{cite web |url=http://www.tennisgrandstand.com/2010/05/19/the-a-z-guide-to-jewish-grand-slam-champions/ |author=David Goodman |title=The A-Z Guide To Jewish Grand Slam Champions |publisher=Tennis Grandstand |date=24 May 2010 |accessdate=4 March 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140304181643/http://www.tennisgrandstand.com/2010/05/19/the-a-z-guide-to-jewish-grand-slam-champions/ |archive-date=4 March 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n* [[Daniel Prenn]], Germany and Britain, highest world ranking, #6\n\n===Track and field===\n* [[Harold Abrahams]], Britain, [[Sprint (running)|sprinter]], Olympic champion ([[100 metre sprint]]) and silver (4x100-m relay) who was immortalized in the film ''Chariots of Fire''<ref>[http://the-internet-eye.com/r-404274/m-VHS/b-169798/a-6300271498/Default.aspx] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928185922/http://the-internet-eye.com/r-404274/m-VHS/b-169798/a-6300271498/Default.aspx |date=28 September 2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://the-internet-eye.com/r-404274/m-VHS/b-169798/a-6300271498/Default.aspx |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2 February 2007 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928185922/http://the-internet-eye.com/r-404274/m-VHS/b-169798/a-6300271498/Default.aspx |archivedate=28 September 2007 }}</ref>\n* Sir [[Sidney Abrahams]], Britain, Olympic [[long jumper]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jewsinsports.org/olympics.asp?sport=olympics&ID=318 |title=Solomon Abrahams |publisher=Jewsinsports.org |date= |accessdate=12 May 2010}}</ref>\n* [[Jo Ankier]], Britain, record holder (1,500m & 3,000m [[steeplechase (athletics)|steeplechase]])<ref>[http://www.thejc.com/home.aspx?ParentId=m14s44&SecId=44&AId=54735&ATypeId=1 The Jewish Chronicle] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071013112702/http://www.thejc.com/home.aspx?ParentId=m14s44&SecId=44&AId=54735&ATypeId=1 |date=13 October 2007 }}</ref>\n*[[Harry Kane (hurdler)|Harry Kane]], Britain, Olympic [[hurdler]]<ref name=\"google1804\">{{cite news|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=883&dat=19540730&id=6vFOAAAAIBAJ&sjid=e0wDAAAAIBAJ&pg=1804,1911973 |title=Eight Jewish Athletes at BEG |publisher=The Canadian Jewish Chronicle |date= 30 July 1954|accessdate=28 October 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Weightlifting===\n* [[Ben Helfgott]], Polish-born British, three-time British champion (lightweight), three-time Maccabiah champion; survived [[Buchenwald]] and [[Theresienstadt concentration camp]]s, as all 