THANIEL|title=ISAACS, NATHANIEL - JewishEncyclopedia.com|website=www.jewishencyclopedia.com}}</ref> explorer\n* [[Aaron Kosminski]], suspect in the Jack the Ripper case\n* [[Gottlieb Wilhelm Leitner]] (1840\u20131899), educationist and orientalist<ref>Oxford [[Dictionary of National Biography]]: \"registered with the Jewish community of Pest\"</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishencyclopedia.com/view.jsp?artid=169&letter=L&search=Leitner|title=LEITNER, GOTTLIEB WILLIAM - JewishEncyclopedia.com|website=www.jewishencyclopedia.com}}</ref>\n* Sir [[Solomon de Medina]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jewishencyclopedia.com/view.jsp?artid=328&letter=M|title=MEDINA, SIR SOLOMON DE - JewishEncyclopedia.com|website=www.jewishencyclopedia.com}}</ref> army contractor, first English Jew to be knighted\n* [[Nigella Lawson]], celebrity chef\n* [[Chava Mond]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.co.il/content.asp?id%3D14439%26sid%3D7 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=18 July 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100626005402/http://www.eonline.co.il/content.asp?id=14439&sid=7 |archivedate=26 June 2010 }}</ref> model\n* [[Dorrit Moussaieff]], Israeli-British businesswoman, entrepreneur, philanthropist and the [[First Lady of Iceland]] \n* [[Yotam Ottolenghi]], celebrity chef, food writer \n* [[Don Pacifico]],<ref>Concise [[Dictionary of National Biography]]: \"a Portuguese Jew, but born a British subject\"</ref> cause of the [[Pacifico incident]]\n* [[Krystyna Skarbek]],<ref>[http://www.lire.fr/critique.asp/idC=39075/idR=217/idG=4 Lire: le magazine litt\u00e9raire]: \"la comtesse Krystyna Skarbek, une aristocrate juive\"</ref> spy\n* Sir [[Bernard Waley-Cohen]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.commentarymagazine.com/Summaries/V38I4P62-1.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2006-04-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050423142301/http://www.commentarymagazine.com/Summaries/V38I4P62-1.htm |archivedate=23 April 2005 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Lord Mayor of London\n\n==See also==\n*[[History of the Jews in England]]\n*[[History of the Jews in Scotland]]\n*[[History of the Jews in Ireland]]\n*[[List of British Jewish entertainers]]\n*[[List of British Jewish nobility and gentry]]\n*[[List of British Jewish politicians]]\n*[[List of British Jewish scientists]]\n*[[List of British Jewish writers]]\n*[[Lists of Jews]]\n*[[List of Britons]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Bibliography===\n*Celmins, Martin. ''Peter Green: The Authorized Biography''. London: Sanctuary Publishing, Ltd.; 3rd edition, 2003. pp.&nbsp;23\u201332.\n* JYB = [[Jewish Year Book]] (annual)\n* \"Obituary: Sir Edward Sassoon\". ''The Times'', Saturday, 25 May 1912; pg. 11; Issue 39908; col C.\n*  TimesAd: ''[[The Times]]'', 6/7/06 p34: \"A Call by Jews in Britain\" (advert signed by 300 British Jews)\n* David S. Katz, ''The Jews in the History of England, 1485\u20131850'' (Oxford: Oxford University Press, 1994). xvi, 447 pp.\n\n{{Lists of Jews by country|noredlinks=yes}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:British Jews}}\n[[Category:Lists of British Jews| ]]\n[[Category:Lists of British people|Jews]]\n[[Category:Lists of Jews]]\n[[Category:Lists of people by ethnicity|Jews]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}}\n{{More citations needed|date=March 2009}}\n{{Jews by country}}\n<!--PLEASE DO NOT ADD ANY MORE NAMES TO THIS PAGE WITHOUT INCLUDING A CREDIBLE SOURCE FOR THE INFORMATION. SEE [[WIKIPEDIA:VERIFIABILITY]] AND [[WIKIPEDIA:NO ORIGINAL RESEARCH]], WHICH ARE POLICY. THE SOURCE MUST SAY THAT THE PERSON IS ACTUALLY JEWISH.-->\n'''List of British Jews''' is a list of prominent [[Jews]] from the [[United Kingdom]] and its [[Countries of the United Kingdom|predecessor states]].\n\nAlthough the first Jews may have arrived on the island of Great Britain with the [[Ancient Rome|Romans]], it was not until the [[Norman Conquest]] of [[William the Conqueror]] in 1066 that organised Jewish communities first appeared in [[England]].  These existed until 1290 when the Jewish population of England was expelled by King [[Edward I of England]].\n\nThere was never a corresponding expulsion from [[Scotland]].  The eminent scholar [[David Daiches]] states in his autobiographical ''Two Worlds: A Scottish born Jewish Childhood'' that there are grounds for saying that Scotland is the only Immigrant country with no history of state persecution of Jews.\n\nJews were re-admitted to England and [[Wales]] in 1656 by [[Oliver Cromwell]].  Slightly more than 200 years later, in 1858 they were [[Jewish emancipation|emancipated]], that is, accepted as full citizens.  In the late 19th century, there was mass Jewish [[immigration]] to England from Russia due to Russian domestic policy.  In the 1930s, the country accepted many refugees from [[Nazism]].  The Jewish population peaked at 450,000, but has since declined due to low birth-rate, [[interfaith marriage|intermarriage]] and [[emigration]], mainly of the younger generation to [[Israel]].  According to the [[United Kingdom Census 2001|2001 census]], the current population is around 295,000, most of whom live in [[London]].\n\n==Academic figures==\n<!--PLEASE DO NOT ADD ANY MORE NAMES TO THIS PAGE WITHOUT INCLUDING A CREDIBLE SOURCE FOR THE INFORMATION. SEE [[WIKIPEDIA:VERIFIABILITY]] AND [[WIKIPEDIA:NO ORIGINAL RESEARCH]], WHICH ARE POLICY. THE SOURCE MUST SAY THAT THE PERSON IS ACTUALLY JEWISH.-->\n\n===Scientists===\n''See [[List of British Jewish scientists]]'', which includes economists.\n\n===Historians===\n<!--PLEASE DO NOT ADD ANY MORE NAMES TO THIS PAGE WITHOUT INCLUDING A CREDIBLE SOURCE FOR THE INFORMATION. SEE [[WIKIPEDIA:VERIFIABILITY]] AND [[WIKIPEDIA:NO ORIGINAL RESEARCH]], WHICH ARE POLICY. THE SOURCE MUST SAY THAT THE PERSON IS ACTUALLY JEWISH.-->\n* [[David Abulafia]], professor of history, University of Cambridge<ref>[[Jewish Year Book|JYB]] 2005 p218</ref>\n* [[Geoffrey Alderman]],<ref>[http://books.guardia