ist (family converted to Anglicanism)\n* [[Hugh Montefiore]],<ref>His own book ''On Being a Jewish Christian'' (1998)</ref> bishop\n* [[Adolf Neubauer]],<ref>[http://www.jewishencyclopedia.com/view.jsp?artid=203&letter=N&search=Neubauer \"Adolf Neubauer\"] ''Jewish Encyclopedia''</ref> Hebraist\n* [[Stefan Reif]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mucjs.org/jhrylands.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2005-12-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20020421173118/http://www.mucjs.org/jhrylands.htm |archivedate=21 April 2002 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Cambridge academic\n* [[Judah Segal]], professor of Semitic languages<ref name=\"JYB 2005 p215\"/>\n* [[Joseph Wolff]],<ref name=\"ReferenceB\"/> missionary\n\n===Others===\n* [[Sidney Greenbaum]], Quain Professor of English Language and Literature, University College London 1983-90 <ref>\"if there was anything invariant in his life, it was his strictly observant devotion to orthodox Judaism\". [https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/obituary-professor-sidney-greenbaum-1349972.html]</ref>\n\n==Artists==\n===Fine arts===\n* [[Frank Auerbach]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.artguide.org/uk/AG.pl?Action=15163A&Axis=AllArtists |title=Archived copy |access-date=29 December 2005 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060103012716/http://www.artguide.org/uk/AG.pl?Action=15163A&Axis=AllArtists |archive-date=3 January 2006 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> painter\n* [[Edith Birkin]], painter<ref name=\"edith\">{{cite web|url=http://gallery.nen.gov.uk/asset669882-.html|title=Birkin, Edith: Liberation Day, 1987|website=NEN Gallery|language=en|access-date=2018-01-28}}</ref>\n* [[David Bomberg]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.modernbritishartists.co.uk/bomberg_biog.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-01-19 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927192257/http://www.modernbritishartists.co.uk/bomberg_biog.htm |archivedate=27 September 2007 }}</ref> painter\n* Sir [[Anthony Caro]]