ishencyclopedia.com/view.jsp?artid=66&letter=A|title=AARON OF LINCOLN - JewishEncyclopedia.com|website=www.jewishencyclopedia.com}}</ref> 12th-century financier\n* [[Moses Haim Montefiore]],<ref>{{cite EB1911|wstitle=Montefiore, Sir Moses Haim|volume=18|page=765}}</ref> financier and philanthropist\n* [[Nathan Mayer Rothschild]],<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|title=House of Rothschild \u2013 MSN Encarta |url=http://encarta.msn.com/encyclopedia_761576222/House_of_Rothschild.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091022001416/http://encarta.msn.com/encyclopedia_761576222/House_of_Rothschild.html |archivedate= 22 October 2009 |url-status=dead }}</ref> financier and banker\n* [[Joseph Salvador]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.shpltd.co.uk/rousseau-jewofcrancourt.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-03-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070702191945/http://www.shpltd.co.uk/rousseau-jewofcrancourt.pdf |archivedate= 2 July 2007 }}</ref> first Jewish director of the [[British East India Company]]\n* [[Baron Swaythling|Barons Swaythling]],<ref name=\"heraldica.org\">{{cite web|url=http://www.heraldica.org/topics/jewish.htm|title=Jewish Heraldry|website=www.heraldica.org}}</ref> bankers\n* [[Samuel Montagu, 1st Baron Swaythling]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.montaguemillennium.com/familyresearch/h_1911_samuel.htm |title=Archived copy |access-date=28 December 2006 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061216144156/http://montaguemillennium.com/familyresearch/h_1911_samuel.htm |archive-date=16 December 2006 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Law===\n* [[John Balcombe|Sir John Balcombe]], Lord Justice of Appeal<ref>''The Guardian'' (Manchester); 04/07/00; Sir Maurice Drake; p20</ref>\n* [[Judah P. Benjamin]], American exile, lawyer<ref>Concise [[Dictionary of National Biography]]: \"born of Jewish parents of English nationality\"</ref>\n* [[Herbert Bentwich]],<ref>[https://www.newyorker.com/fact/content/articles/021209fa_fact New